(server - tracker)
(desktop - desktop client)
(android - android client)



-------------------------------------------------------------------
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~First connect~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Desktop connects to server and tells it's id
2. Server checks if there is already the same id and ip
3. If the same ip exists replace id with the new one and vice versa
4. Desktop shows qrcode with it's id & pub_key and tracker's ip and ports
5. Android scans qrcode
6. Android connects to server asking for id's ip and ports
7. Android connects with this data to Desktop and sends its pubkey
8. Now they ping each other :3
-------------------------------------------------------------------



-------------------------------------------------------------------
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~Sending  data~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Encrypt with your private key
3. Attach your id(may be shortened)
2. Send to all your connections (TODO: more than 1)
-------------------------------------------------------------------



-------------------------------------------------------------------
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Server~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Store ids with ips and ports
2. Send ips with ports when id
3. Update ids and ips list
4. Ping ips and remove dead ones
-------------------------------------------------------------------



-------------------------------------------------------------------
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~Android~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Check for notifications
2. Send it

